ithm, not the human, the star merchant.

And yet, merchandising has always been driven by data. What=E2=80=99s chang=
ed is that many brands rely on data, and data only, resulting in product th=
at=E2=80=99s flat-out boring and devoid of personality. That=E2=80=99s what=
=E2=80=99s different about Popular Culture, the holdco run by Jens and Emma=
 Grede, the couple behind everything from Frame denim (which Jens founded i=
n 2012 with best friend and longtime business
partner Erik Torstensson, who still runs it) to Kardashian vehicles such as=
 Good American and Khy. The Gredes also recently invested in Elder Statesma=
n, Calabasas hometown hero Greg Chait=E2=80=99s ode to cashmere.

